# Implementation Plan - Phase 13: Song Search & Setlist Workflow

Enhance the library management and projection workflow with dual-filter search, a quick-preview lyrics panel, and a dedicated setlist (middle section) to track songs added for the session.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> To support the new workflow, I will update how songs are managed:
> 1. **Clicking a song in the library**: Opens the **Lyrics Preview Pane** at the bottom of the library (Left Section).
> 2. **Clicking '+' or pressing 'Enter'**: Adds the song to the **Setlist** (Middle Section) AND immediately appends its slides to the **Slides Section** (Right Section).
> 3. **Continuous Slides**: The Right Section will show slides for ALL songs in the setlist, with each song separated by a blank slide.
> 4. **Search Performance**: I will implement debounced dual-filtering for fast searching.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Search & Data Logic

#### [MODIFY] `lib/features/songs/domain/song_repository.dart`
- Update `searchSongs` to accept optional `titleQuery` and `lyricsQuery`.

#### [MODIFY] `lib/features/songs/data/isar_song_repository.dart`
- Implement the dual-filter logic. If both are provided, it will find songs matching BOTH (Intersection).

#### [MODIFY] `lib/features/songs/presentation/song_providers.dart`
- Add `titleSearchProvider` and `lyricsSearchProvider` (StateProviders).
- Update `SongListNotifier` to watch both search providers and trigger searches.

### 2. Setlist & Selection State

#### [MODIFY] `lib/features/songs/presentation/song_selection_providers.dart`
- Rename `selectedSongProvider` to `previewSongProvider`.
- Add `setlistProvider` (StateNotifierProvider) to manage the list of songs for the session.
- Update `currentSlidesProvider` (in live_controller) to flatten all songs in the setlist into a single list of slides.

### 3. UI Components

#### [MODIFY] `lib/features/songs/presentation/song_library_tab.dart`
- **Dual Search UI**: Two compact `TextField` widgets at the top.
- **Lyrics Preview Pane**: 
    - A panel at the bottom of the tab that appears when a song is clicked.
    - Displays full lyrics with a scrollbar and a close button.
    - **Keyword Highlighting**: Matches from the lyrics search box will be highlighted in yellow.
- **List Items**: 
    - Add a `+` button for adding to the setlist.
    - Support for `Enter` key to add the selected song.

#### [NEW] `lib/features/dashboard/presentation/widgets/setlist_pane.dart`
- The middle section of the dashboard.
- Lists titles of songs added to the session.
- Allows reordering (future) or removing songs.
- Selection here updates `activeSongProvider`.

#### [MODIFY] `lib/features/dashboard/presentation/pages/main_dashboard_page.dart`
- Integrate `SetlistPane` into the layout.

#### [MODIFY] `lib/features/dashboard/presentation/widgets/preview_pane.dart`
- Update to watch `activeSongProvider` instead of the old `selectedSongProvider`.

## Implementation Details

### Highlight Generator
I will implement a `RichText` helper that uses `RegExp` to find all occurrences of the search term and builds a list of `TextSpan` objects with either normal or highlighted styles.

### Layout Density
To keep the UI clean, the search boxes and preview pane will use high-density styling (low padding, small fonts) consistent with the VS Code / OpenSong aesthetic.

